<span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii"></span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p1"></span> <span id="page_509">p.
509</span> <span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-Page_509"></span><span
class="c4"><span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p1.1"></span>Canon CXXXVII. 
(Continuation of the last in the Greek.)</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p2"></span>*Here begin the examples of the
Nicene Council, sent on the sixth day before the calends of December in
the year 419,* <span id="fr_493"></span>[494](#fn_493.md) *after the
consulate of the most glorious emperor Honorius for the <span
class="sc"><span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p3.1"></span>XII</span>th time,
and Theodosius for the <span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p3.2"></span>IX</span>th time,* <span
id="fr_494"></span>[495](#fn_494.md) *Augustuses, to Boniface the bishop of
the City of Rome.*

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p5"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p5.1"></span>We</span> believe in one God etc.…the
Catholic and Apostolic Church anathematizes them. <span
id="fr_495"></span>[496](#fn_495.md)

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p7"></span>To this symbol of the faith there
were also annexed copies of the statutes of the same Nicene Councils
from the aforenamed pontiffs, in all respects as are contained above;
which we do not think it necessary to write out here again.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p8"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p8.1"></span>Notes.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p9"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p9.1"></span>Ancient Epitome of Canon
CXXXVII.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p10"></span>The Canons of the Synod of Nice
are sent, as they were decreed by the Fathers, in accordance with your
letters.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.cxxxviii-p11"></span>\[Here follows the Nicene Creed
in full.\]

